#Reliance   Reliance #Q1FY24 Performance  Oil 2 Chemical segment: ‚Ä¢)PAT declining 6% year-on-year due to a sharp decline in oil to chemicals revenues because of 31% fall in crude oil prices.  ‚Ä¢)EBITDA grew by 5% Year-on-Year due to higher production in the oil & gas segment led.  ‚Ä¢)Rise in finance costs due to higher interest rates and loan balances has led to decline in PAT( net profit ).  ‚Ä¢)Diversified revenue streams with strong performances by retail and telecom helped RIL to manage the O2C segment impact on its Q1-FY24 performance.  ‚Ä¢)O2C business revenue dipped 17.7% over Q1-FY23, for the second consecutive quarter.  Telecom Segment: ‚Ä¢)The company( jio-Telecom segment ) registered a significant improvement led by the addition of 29 million subscribers, higher data consumption due to 5G adoption, and a 3% improvement in ARPU.  Retail Segment: ‚Ä¢)Revenues grew by 20% driven by a rapid expansion in the retail space area, while revenue per square feet continued to be moderate.  ‚Ä¢)The Grocery business led the growth by 59% YoY growth in the Smart and the Smart Bazaars.  ‚Ä¢)The Fashion and lifestyle business grew 15% YoY, driven by a pick-up in store traffic as well as average bill value.   ‚Ä¢)The digital and new commerce business( jio Mart & Ajio ) continued to grow contributing 18% of the revenues.  Conclusion: Performance of legacy businesses ( O2C Segment )was Slow down in Q1 FY24 and the new-age businesses, such as retail, media, digital, and renewables, would continue to drive the Business Growth.
